         <abstract>
            <p>It is shown, using the Rayleigh-Ritz method of the calculus of variations, that an upper bound for the first zero $j_\nu$, of $z^{-\nu}J_\nu(z), \nu &gt; -1$, is given by $$(\nu + 1)^{1/2}\{(\nu + 2)^{1/2} + 1\},$$ and that for large $\nu, j_\nu = \nu + O(\nu^{1/2})$.</p>
          </abstract>
